<h3>BreathAR: Leveraging Breathing as a Hands-free Interface for Augmented Reality.</h3>

<p>It is about a new AR interaction modality that interfaces with breathing as the directly controlled signal.</p>

<p>Since the experience of typical AR interfaces based on interaction modalities like hand gestures and voice is not perfect. Users often face problems like a slow response, and easy misoperation, and find it difficult to interact with distant objects. To solve these issues, We utilize the rich interaction space in breathing and built a detection model and a user interface. with our system, users can achieve all AR interactions quickly, accurately, efficiently, and intuitively through breathing.</p>

<p>We have built this system on Hololens2 that allows us to perform all basic UI operations such as select, click, zoom, scroll and rotate.</p>